# Resistance Indicator Layer — Technical Addendum

## Lifeline Chronic Care and Recovery Platform

**Document Version:** 1.2  
**Classification:** Client-Confidential  
**Grant Reference:** RHN-BEHAV-2026-024  
**Date:** 2025-07-15

---

## 1. Overview

This addendum specifies the Resistance Indicator Layer (RIL), a clinical risk augmentation that identifies patients exhibiting behavioral patterns suggesting resistance to treatment engagement, care plan adherence, or clinical outreach. Patients with elevated resistance signals are automatically escalated to a Higher-Touch Management Track (HTMT) with increased supervision requirements and care team visibility.

### 1.1 Design Principles

| Principle | Application |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Clinical sensitivity** | Resistance indicators are framed as engagement barriers, not patient defects |
| **Multi-indicator fusion** | No single behavior triggers escalation; patterns across dimensions are required |
| **Care team awareness** | Resistance signals are surfaced as clinical observations, not alerts |
| **Recovery-oriented** | Escalation triggers additional support resources, not restrictions |
| **Override capability** | Clinicians may adjust track assignment based on clinical judgment |

---

## 2. Resistance Indicator Taxonomy

### 2.1 Indicator Categories

| Category | Code | Description | Clinical Significance |
|----------|------|-------------|----------------------|
| **Care Plan Disagreement** | CPD-001 | Patient explicitly disagrees with ≥3 care plan elements in single review | May indicate misaligned treatment goals |
| **Care Plan Disagreement** | CPD-002 | Patient requests removal of ≥2 care plan items after initial agreement | May indicate deteriorating insight |
| **Symptom Denial** | SYD-001 | Patient consistently rates symptoms 0/10 despite clinical evidence of severity | May indicate lack of insight (anosognosia) |
| **Symptom Denial** | SYD-002 | Patient declines to complete symptom assessments in ≥3 consecutive attempts | May indicate avoidance or distrust |
| **Symptom Denial** | SYD-003 | Patient explicitly states "nothing is wrong" when clinical record shows recent crisis | May indicate acute deterioration |
| **Outreach Avoidance** | OAV-001 | Patient ignores ≥5 outreach attempts within 14-day window | May indicate disengagement from care |
| **Outreach Avoidance** | OAV-002 | Patient explicitly requests no contact via patient portal | May indicate treatment ambivalence |
| **Outreach Avoidance** | OAV-003 | Patient provides invalid contact information for ≥2 outreach channels | May indicate passive disengagement |
| **Appointment Resistance** | APR-001 | Patient cancels ≥3 appointments within 30 days without rescheduling | May indicate barriers to engagement |
| **Appointment Resistance** | APR-002 | Patient "no-shows" to ≥2 consecutive appointments | High-risk disengagement pattern |

