## 5. Therapeutic Alliance Risk Stratification

### 5.1 Conceptual Framework: Engagement Barriers vs. Clinical Risk

The system distinguishes between **clinical destabilization** (symptom severity) and **therapeutic alliance strain** (engagement barriers). While distinct, correlation between these streams triggers the **Intensive Care Coordination Track** (ICCT).

**Design Principle:** Resistance indicators are modeled as *barriers to effective care delivery* requiring clinical adaptation, not as compliance failures warranting punitive escalation. All ICCT transitions require human clinical validation to prevent algorithmic pathologization of legitimate autonomy.

